---
import Base from '../../layouts/PlottedBase.astro';
---

<Base title="About · Plotted" description="What Plotted is and how it's made.">
  <main class="about measure">
    <p class="kicker" data-reveal>About</p>
    <h1 data-reveal>One dataset, one story, made by hand.</h1>
    <div class="prose" data-reveal>
      <p>
        <strong>Plotted</strong> is a gallery of data visualizations built from
        the ground up, with no dashboards and no templates. Each piece takes a
        single public dataset and tries to say one true, self-contained thing
        with it, designed to be read rather than filtered.
      </p>
      <p>
        The aim sits between two references: the interactivity of a good data
        dashboard and the authored, editorial craft of designers like Federica
        Fragapane. Every piece names its source and license, and is built with
        Astro and D3 with the type set by hand.
      </p>
      <p>
        By <a href="https://anthonyabusa.com">Anthony Busa</a>. More things to
        use live at <a href="https://anthonyabusa.com/apps">anthonyabusa.com/apps</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .about { width: var(--frame); max-width: var(--measure); margin: 0 auto; }
  .about h1 { font-size: var(--step-4); margin: var(--space-2) 0 var(--space-4); }
  .prose p { font-size: var(--step-1); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 var(--space-3); }
  .prose a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
  .prose a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
